messages.message: @Jet The current CI/CD doesn't offer rollback option in the development phase. It is because the commit to the Github is a manual step, there is no automatic sync between AIHub instance and the VCS. We offer only App rollback in the target environment.
Thank you, I’ll reply back with our partner.
when you said "App rollback", it's this right?

For the productized version in the same environment (using Production Workspaces & Deployments - see launch comms & walkthrough video: https://instabase.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/GTM1/pages/3077931010/Release+25.30+Aug+4+2025#Link-Deployments-To-Prod-Workspaces
), there isn’t a dedicated rollback button. However, you can update a deployment to use an older app version if a mistake was made. You’ll also be able to view the app schemas for those older versions, though there’s no way to roll back the project’s configuration itself to a previous version.
